text: George Patrick Tory (3 June 1899 – 29 March 1952) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood in the Victorian Football League (VFL). He later played for Hawthorn in the Victorian Football Association. == Notes == == External links == * *George Tory's profile at Collingwood Forever Category:1899 births Category:1952 deaths Category:People from Omeo Category:Australian rules footballers from Victoria (Australia) Category:Collingwood Football Club players Category:Hawthorn Football Club (VFA) players Category:Australian military personnel of World War I
